Design and develop embedded software used to control  machinery. Other responsibilities may include items such as commercial software projects, automated test scripts, and software maintenance. On-site software modifications during machine commissioning and maintenance may be required.  
 Help develop strategies to increase quality and efficiencies in the software organization.
• Design and develop embedded machine control solutions for railway maintenance equipment
• Design and implement graphical user interfaces
• Distributed I/O controls experience is a plus
• Support hydraulic and electrical controls engineering

Examples of the Machine Control SW:
Embedded software development in C/C++/Matlab; Embedded microprocessor MPC555/MAC7131;
Simulink/Stateflow model development;
NI software development tool ( Labview,
Veristand);
Revision control(Rational Clearcase);
CAN, J1939
bus communication and development tool (Vector CANape, CANalyzer, ATI Vision);
